{{Infobox sport governing body |name= Centro Universitario Sportivo Italiano |logo= |logosize= |sport= [[Category:Multi-sport clubs|Multisport]] |abbrev = CUSI |founded = 1946 |aff = [[Italian National Olympic Committee]] |affdate = |region = |regionyear = |location = [[Rome]] |president = Lorenzo Lentini |chairman = |chiefexec = |secretary = |coach = |womenscoach = |replaced = |prevfounded = |url = http://www.cusi.it |countryflag= Italy }} The '''Centro Universitario Sportivo Italiano''' (CUSI), (English: ''Italian University Sports Centre)'' is an association that promotes sports activity at the university level, and is recognized by the [[Italian National Olympic Committee]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.coni.it/it/enti-di-promozione-sportiva/centro-universitario-sportivo-italiano-cusi.html?view=organosportivo&id=69|title=Centro Universitario Sportivo Italiano|publisher=coni.it|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref>
It is headquartered in Rome, Via Angelo Brofferio 7. The current president is Lorenzo Lentini.
==Committees for university sports== Most Italian universities have a CUS (''Comitato per lo sport Universitario''). As of September 2017, there were 48 such committees. <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cusi.it/SITO/chi-siamo/i-cus|title=I CUS|publisher=coni.it|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref>
==Activity== Every year since 1947, when the first event was held in Bologna, the CUSI organizes the [[Italian University Championships|Campionati Nazionali Universitari]] (''National University Championships'').
