{{Infobox Stadium | stadium_name = Century Lotus Stadium | nickname = 世纪莲 | image = [[File:Century Lotus Stadium.jpg|300px]] | location = {{Flagicon|China}} [[Foshan]], [[China]] | broke_ground = | opened = 2006 | closed = | demolished = | owner = City of Foshan | operator = | surface = Grass | construction_cost = [[Chinese yuan|¥ 939 million CNY]] | architect = GMP Architects | former_names = | tenants = | seating_capacity = 36,686<ref name="fs218">[https://web.archive.org/web/20111022194141/http://www.fs218.com/zhanlan/shijilian.html 佛山世纪莲体育中心介绍]</ref> }}
'''Century Lotus Stadium''' ({{zh|s= 世纪莲体育场}}) is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Foshan]], [[China]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches. The stadium holds 36,686 people and was built in 2005. It hosted a first round match between [[China national football team|China]] and [[Myanmar national football team|Myanmar]] during [[2010 FIFA World Cup qualification (AFC First Round)|2010 FIFA World Cup]] qualifying. This building has a design similar to the reconstructed [[Jawaharlal Nehru Stadium, Delhi]] built by the same designers.
