'''Isnardo "Junior" Faro''' (born 15 July 1978) is a weightlifter who competed at two [[Summer Olympics]] for [[Aruba]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Junior Faro, Bio|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/fa/junior-faro-1.html|website=Olympics at Sports-Reference.com|accessdate=29 January 2017}}</ref>

==Career==
Aged 18 years old Faro went to [[Atlanta, Georgia|Atlanta]], [[United States]] to compete in the [[1996 Summer Olympics]], he entered the [[Weightlifting at the 1996 Summer Olympics – Men's 76 kg|middleweight]] division and he finished 21st out of the 24 starters.<ref>{{cite web|title=Weightlifting at the 1996 Atlanta Summer Games: Men's Middleweight|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/summer/1996/WLT/mens-middleweight.html|website=Olympics at Sports-Reference.com|accessdate=3 February 2017}}</ref>
Eight years later he competed at the [[2004 Summer Olympics]] held in [[Athens]], [[Greece]], this time he was competing in the [[Weightlifting at the 2004 Summer Olympics – Men's 94 kg|middle-heavyweight]] division, this time he finished 19th out of the 25 lifters that started the event.<ref>{{cite web|title=Weightlifting at the 2004 Athina Summer Games: Men's Middle-Heavyweight|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/summer/2004/WLT/mens-middle-heavyweight.html|website=Olympics at Sports-Reference.com|accessdate=3 February 2017}}</ref>

